      • buildDescriptions

        public abstract ColumnDescription[] buildDescriptions()
        This method builds the ColumnDescription[] that describes the current plug-in table column state. This is used to build the initial mapping to a table variable, and to perform model validation.

      • getTableData

        public java.lang.Object[][] getTableData()
        This method may be overridden to return the current set of tabular data in the plug-in. This will allow the table variable creator to initialize the table data automatically.

      • getExpectedRowCount

        public int getExpectedRowCount()
        This method returns the expected number of rows for a fixed length table. This value should be -1 for a variable length table. This value is used to limit the selection of available table values, and for model validation checks.
        Returns:
        the expected number of rows for a fixed-length table, or -1 for a variable-length table.

      • findColumnIndex

        Finds the index in the mapping to the selected column name. This will return -1 if there is no mapping to the given column name.

      • findMappedColumn

        public int findMappedColumn​(java.lang.String name)
        Finds the index in the column mapping that matches the provided name. The name is the column label for the plug-in table. The returned index is the index into the mapping array that matches the provided name. If none exists a -1 will be returned instead.
        Parameters:
        name - the plug-in table column name.
        Returns:
        the index into the mapping array for the given name.

      • getColumn

        public NumericsTableColumn getColumn​(java.lang.String name)
        Attempts to find the column in the Table variable that is mapped to the provided plug-in table column name. This will return null if the column does not exist.
        Parameters:
        name - the plug-in table column name.
        Returns:
        the NumericsTableColumn in the referenced table variable that has been mapped to the requested plug-in column name. If none exists, this will return null.

      • parseMappingTagStart

        public boolean parseMappingTagStart​(java.lang.String[] comments)
        Attempts to read in the values in the mapping tab into the current table reference object. No modification is done to the table data, this is initializing the values inside this TableReference from the text in the comments. If this returns false, the table reference is either invalid or non-existent. This method will print errors in the case of an invalid table reference.
        Parameters:
        comments - the String[] of comments from the ASCII file.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the comments contain a valid table reference.
